<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CAHILL UPSETS MAYOTTE IN FIRST ROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Australian Darren Cahill upset 14th-seeded Tim Mayotte, 1-6, 6-4, 7-5, and 
Marcus Ondruska eliminated No. 16 Petr Korda, 6-3, 4-6, 7-5, in the first round 
of the $1.3-million Assn. of Tennis Professionals Championship Tuesday at 
Mason, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
French Open champion Andres Gomez of Ecuador recovered from a second-set lapse 
to gain a 6-3, 7-6 (7-5) victory over Dan Goldie, and second-seeded Andre 
Agassi, who lost the French Open final to Gomez, advanced with a 6-4, 6-3 win 
over Richey Reneberg. 
</P>
<P>
In other matches, 10th-seeded Pete Sampras beat David Pate, 7-6 (7-5), 6-4, and 
15th-seeded Richard Fromberg of Australia downed Czechoslovakia's Karel 
Novacek, 3-6, 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Laura Gildemeister of Peru survived a tough match under the 
scorching sun and defeated Sara Gomer of Britain, 6-4, 7-6 (9-7), in a $150,000 
Virginia Slims tournament at Albuquerque, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round matches, top-seeded Jana Novotna of Czechoslovakia 
trounced Carrie Cunningham, 6-0, 6-1, and eighth-seeded Anne Minter of 
Australia overcame Robyn Field of South Africa, 6-3, 4-6, 6-1. 
</P>
