<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: CATFISH AT MOST SITES; STRIPERS IN SOME AREAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's catfish and more catfish at most Southland reservoirs, but two offer an 
alternative -- striped bass. 
</P>
<P>
The bite is rated fair at San Bernardino County's Silverwood Lake, where Paul 
Offerdahl of Mira Loma caught a 26-pound striper. In Los Angeles County's 
Pyramid Lake, Ed Kurihara of Monterey Park took 14-, nine- and five-pound 
stripers, while Ernie Benabidez of La Crescenta landed a 15 1/2-pounder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080890-0042 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 258542 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 8, 1990, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
