<HEADLINE>
<P>
SLADE'S HOME RUN LIFTS WOODLAND HILLS TO LITTLE LEAGUE WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jesse Slade led off the bottom of the sixth inning with a home run to send 
Woodland Hills to a 3-2 victory over Rancho Penasquitos on Tuesday in the 
consolation semifinal of the state Division 2 Little League baseball tournament 
at Stearns Park in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Left-hander Jared Sandler, who struck out nine and allowed one hit, picked up 
the win in the game for all-star players aged 11-12 . 
</P>
</TEXT>
