<TEXT>
<P>
Bank of America, San Francisco, has named Ed Hall senior vice president and 
head of consumer marketing for the Consumer Banking Group. 
</P>
<P>
Hall, 48, will be responsible for all consumer marketing, including 
advertising, in California. He replaces Shelly Porges, who left the bank to 
start her own business. Hall joins the bank from First Constitutional Bank of 
New Haven, Conn., where he was responsible for marketing, advertising and 
public relations. 
</P>
