<TEXT>
<P>
Quaker Oats Co.: The food concern said its fiscal-year earnings fell 17% to 
$169 million on revenue that was flat at $3.6 billion. The Chicago-based 
company, which is restructuring to refocus on its core food business, said the 
results included a $60-million charge for discontinued, non-food operations. 
