<P>
The editor of the Financial Times, Sir Geoffrey Owen, is stepping down after 10 
years in the job. Owen will be succeeded in January by the present deputy 
editor, Richard Lambert. A statement issued by the Financial Times said Owen, 
56, would join the Center for Economic Performance at the London School of 
Economics next April. 
