<TEXT>
<P>
Police have released a composite drawing of the suspect in last week's Newport 
Beach jewelry heist. 
</P>
<P>
The man, who entered the store Jewels by Mondonna at about 11 a.m. on July 31, 
posed as a customer before pulling out a handgun and forcing the two store 
employees to the rear of the shop. He tied up the two workers and then fled, 
stealing an undetermined amount of jewelry. 
</P>
<P>
