<P>
OIL FLOW FROM IRAQ HALTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DUBAI, United Arab Emirates 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
q's oil exports came to a complete halt today as a world embargo took hold 
after its invasion of Kuwait. 
</P>
<P>
Oil industry sources said no Iraqi oil was leaving Turkey or Saudi Arabia, 
which carry nearly 90% of Baghdad's exports by pipeline, nor was any oil 
leaving Iraq by sea. 
</P>
<P>
Oil is Iraq's main source of foreign exchange, and a prolonged embargo could 
destroy its economy. It was exporting 2.7 million barrels per day -- 5% of 
world output. 
</P>
