<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAY DAUGHTER OF MR. PROSPECTOR SOLD FOR $1.2 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A bay daughter of Mr. Prospector brought the top price of $1.2 million during 
Tuesday's opening session of the Fasig Tipton Saratoga thoroughbred yearling 
sale. 
</P>
<P>
The filly was purchased by Luca Cumani as agent for a buyer who wasn't 
identified. 
</P>
<P>
The filly was consigned by White Birch Farm, which also offered a bay filly by 
Nijinsky II that went for $1.1 million to Tom Skiffington. 
</P>
<P>
Fifty-three yearlings sold for $12.54 million, an average of $236,717 per 
transaction. Last year's opening session brought in $12.92 million, with an 
average of $339,526 per lot. The sale continues today and Thursday in the Fasig 
Tipton Center near Saratoga Race Course. 
</P>
</TEXT>
